OL,3,CEnergy bills to rise by more than
OL,4,Cexpected as Ofgem increases price cap
OL,6,FCampaigners have criticised the higher
OL,7,Fthan expected price cap, saying the
OL,8,Fenergy industry is making billions in
OL,9,Fprofits, ITV News Consumer Editor
OL,10,FChris Choi reports
OL,12,FEnergy prices will rise by 6.4% in
OL,13,FApril under energy watchdog Ofgem's
OL,14,Fnew price cap, representing a higher-
OL,15,Fthan-expected rise in energy bills.
OL,17,FOfgem said the rise will equate to
OL,18,F#111 for an average household per
OL,19,Fyear, or around #9.25 a month, over
OL,20,Fthe three-month period of the price
OL,21,Fcap.
