OL,3,CEnergy bills to rise by more than
OL,4,Cexpected as Ofgem increases price cap
OL,6,FThe increase means the total average
OL,7,Fbill will rise from #1,738 to #1,849
OL,8,Ffrom April 1 for a typical household
OL,9,Fin England, Scotland and Wales.
OL,11,FExperts had forecast bills to rise by
OL,12,Fabout 5%, because of an increase in
OL,13,Fgas prices across Europe, caused by a
OL,14,Fslump in the amount of gas held in
OL,15,Fstorage across the continent.
OL,17,FThe energy price cap sets a maximum
OL,18,Fprice that energy companies can charge
OL,19,Fpeople in England, Scotland and Wales
OL,20,Ffor each unit of energy they use.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/15
